title: Wisconsin Firm Recalls Liver PatE Due to Misbranding and An Undeclared Allergen
summary: WASHINGTON, Feb. 2, 2013 -Nueske's Applewood Smoked Meats, a Wittenberg, Wis. establishment, is recalling approximately 4,454 pounds of liver patE products because they are misbranded in that they contain the milk protein sodium caseinate, a known allergen, which is not declared on the product label...
impacted_products: 10-oz. vacuum packed packages of "Nueske's Applewood Smoked Liver Paté"
